author: Mike Foss
title: The 7 freshest college football uniforms of Week 5
text:
The 7 freshest college football uniforms of Week 5 USA Today Sports 1 day ago Mike Foss
Week 5 went down in the books as the most tumultuous of the season to date. No one is entirely sure who belongs in the playoff … no one is entirely sure who belongs in the Top 25 for that matter. One thing we do know is that teams wore uniforms, and these seven looked the best.
AdChoices 7. Florida © Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports All-orange is a good look. So is knocking off the SEC favorite.
6. Baylor
© Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports I don’t fully understand everything that’s happening with this Baylor uniform. I also don’t fully understand abstract art. It doesn’t make either less of a masterpiece.
5. Northwestern
© Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports
If in doubt, wear all black. When you wear all black, you look like Batman.
4. Maryland
© Provided by USA Today Sports AP Maryland is a terrible football team but they remain one of the best dressed, for whatever that’s worth.
3. N.C. State
© Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports There is a lot of fun happening here, N.C. State. A lot of frolicking style if there ever was.
2. Miami
© Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports This is an incredible look.
1. Arizona State
© Provided by USA Today Sports USA TODAY Sports This might be my favorite uniform of the season. There isn’t a weak point in the ensemble. Everything works together and nothing is overdone.
